									<p class="bodynoindent"><img src="../../page_elements/content_bullet.gif" width="5" height="5"> <b>General Aspects:</b> On its famous bay, with the smaller Gulf of Pozzuoli to the west and to the southeast - the more extended indentation of the Gulf of Salerno--the city is situated between two areas of volcanic activity: Mount Vesuvius to the east and the Campi Flegrei (Phlegraean Fields) to the northwest.<br>
									</p>
